President Donald J. Trump will award the Presidential Medal of Freedom to Arthur B. Laffer on June 19, 2019. The Presidential Medal of Freedom is the highest civilian honor in the United States and is given to individuals who have made significant contributions to the security or national interests of the country, world peace, or significant public or private endeavors. Arthur B. Laffer is known as the "Father of Supply-Side Economics" and is one of the most influential economists in American history. He is famous for his economic theory, the "Laffer Curve," which demonstrates the positive impact of lower tax rates on investment, production, jobs, wages, economic growth, and tax compliance. Dr. Laffer has had a distinguished career, serving as the first chief economist of the Office of Management and Budget and as a top economic advisor to President Ronald Reagan. He has also provided consulting services to the Department of the Treasury and Department of Defense. Through his public service and contributions to economic policy, Dr. Laffer has played a role in promoting prosperity in the United States.